analysis: The agent used the function education_schedule_student_events_1 instead of the correct function E_S_S_E, despite both offering identical scheduling capabilities. The error stems from selecting the wrong function name, not from the function arguments.

The agent added extra unsupported parameters ("resolution" and "cloudCoverage") to the SA_HI function call instead of only using the parameters specified in the tool description and expected answer, resulting in a mismatch and failed function call.

The agent called the function security_generate_alias_1 instead of the correct S_G_A tool, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function call despite supplying the correct parameters. The failure was due to selecting the wrong function name.

The agent failed to include the required "schedule" parameter specifying the daily 6:00 AM test run time, omitting a key part of the user's instruction to automate and schedule the tests as requested.
The agent provided the genre as "pop" (lowercase) instead of "Pop" (title case), resulting in a parameter mismatch with the expected function call, which required an exact match in case sensitivity.

The agent called the wrong function, using "presentation_add_background_music_1" instead of "P_A_B_M" as required, despite both having similar descriptions and the expected call specifying "P_A_B_M". This indicates a failure in function selection.

The agent incorrectly included an "eventTypes" argument in the CTG_T function call, which is not part of the expected or supported parameters, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function signature.
The agent incorrectly called the "football_venue_management_1" function instead of the required "F_V_M" function, failing to use the expected tool even though both provide the same capabilities.

The agent called the function "olympics_get_top_athletes_1" instead of the available and expected function "O_G_T_A" as specified in the tools list, despite both providing the same functionality, resulting in a function call mismatch.

The agent incorrectly included extra simulation features ("gravity simulation", "density mapping", "fragmentation algorithms", "3D visualization") in the function call arguments, resulting in a parameter mismatch with the expected S_E_S function signature. The function should only receive the specified cloud and simulation parameters.

The agent incorrectly included extra parameters ("sources", "keywords", "include_multimedia") not required by the expected function signature, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function call format and failure to match the evaluator's criteria.

The agent used the wrong function (TimeTravelGeocoder_getAddress_1) instead of the required TTG_A function, and also did not match the expected parameter formats (e.g., slight differences in coordinates and date formatting for year 100).

The agent incorrectly made a single batch call with multiple patient IDs using "hospital_record_fetch_1" instead of issuing individual calls (one per patient) to the "H_R_F" function as expected. It failed to match the required function granularity and selection.
